data.description:
UPDATE ALERT!

JUST GOT APPROVED BY INSURANCE FOR A BRAND-NEW TPO ROOF! The roof, made out of high-tech TPO which is a godsend for flat roofs---it can be contoured to make water drain correctly; it is virtually invulnerable to hail; and it comes with a transferrable warranty---has an estimated value of $32,000.

. . . but the price remains at $295,000.

It's almost a miracle---snap, just like that:  instant equity of $32,000 and no increase in price at all. 

Now let's get back to the description of the house:

The jewel of Enchanted Hills---one of Roswell's premier neighborhoods!

(For some reason not all the pics would load---especially bathroom pics, for some reson---so here is a complete array: https://imgur.com/a/ObyOlhK)

This is one of the very few two-story homes in the entire neighborhood, on one of the most beautiful streets in Roswell. It is a 2,444 square foot home that was renovated to a very high standard; I expected to live here for the rest of my life so no "flip" techniques or products were used. 

Everything, or nearly everything, in this house is brand-new and the improvements are all top notch. In the last three years these renovations and enhancements include:

---brand new central air conditioning system by Fulkerson (new compressor, new furnace, everything) 

---brand new mini-split air conditioning system also by Fulkerson in master bedroom and also in the master bath (this is probably the best air-conditioned house in Roswell)

---new floors in nearly every room of the house

---new paint nearly everywhere

---popcorn ceilings scraped and resurfaced

---new water softener system

---new staircase

---new master bedroom

---new master bath (most of those pics wouldn't load for some reason; please see https://imgur.com/a/ObyOlhK)

---new guest room/yoga room

---new guest bath (these pics also wouldn't load; please see https://imgur.com/a/ObyOlhK)

---new living room (with cathedral ceiling, which is GREAT for keeping things cool in summer)

---brand new hand-crafted butcher block-topped island in kitchen (I've retained the original 1980s counter tops because they're in such dynamite shape; I've also retained the period-correct doorknobs throughout the house because they're perfect)

---new grass in front and back

---problem trees removed

---new washing machine/dryer, new Bosch dishwasher, new Frigidaire oven/stove (oven never used even once); all appliances stay with the house

---refinished exterior stucco

Other highlights (not added by me) include: 

---sprinkler system in front and back yard

---walk-in closet in master bedroom

---very good closet space in two guest bedrooms

---separate linen closets and medicine closets upstairs and downstairs

---huge brick patio in back

---six-foot privacy wall surrounding entire (and very large) back yard

---a laundry room that is so big you could use it as an office or 4th bedroom

---a three-car garage (or maybe a spacious two-car garage if you drive big vehicles)

It is one of the most beautiful homes in Roswell renovated to a very high standard both inside and out. 

Come and see for yourself and fall in love.
data.whatILove:
This was meant to be a rest-of-my-life home, so all the very extensive renovations were done with an eye to quality and longevity. I skimped on nothing. The interior is exquisite; the exterior is in near-perfect shape; the lawn---especially by New Mexico standards---is like a putting green. 

It's got a huge back yard (I think the size that's quoted here on Zillow is wrong; I need to look into those records; the yard is a double-sized corner lot) with a 6-foot tall privacy wall that is ideal for entertaining. 

The kitchen is spacious and has tons of storage and counter-space. 

The master suite is 600 square feet and waking up there makes you feel like an emperor. (I'm highly frustrated that I can't get all the bathroom pics to load; please check https://imgur.com/a/ObyOlhK for those pics.) 

The living room is tied with the master bedroom (and master bath) as my favorite room in the house; it's enormous and light-filled and the fireplace in the wintertime is magical. (Although the fireplace in the bedroom is great too.)

It's a perfect house for a family or just someone who likes a lot of space and a quiet, perfect neighborhood on the edge of town with a view of Capitan and instant access to the bypass. 

It's a gem. 

Come see it for yourself!
